90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gW3EFcU</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[vidadobl6]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Crane operators: The unsung Heroes against Melanoma</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/qr2DkIR</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6ep1gVx.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qr2DkIR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ALDSS]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Puppy day?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Wek3PYg</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MFapamz.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Wek3PYg</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ultraruben]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Girl power</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Fl9lyRo</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Yoz7c5U.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Most of my customers don't care who works on their computer or ask me IT questions all the time without assuming I'm a secretary. But at least once a day I get the "I need to talk to the guy" person who won't listen, isn't interested in hearing I am the tech, belittle me, or by god they need to hear what I said but in a man's voice.
I had four people ask for "the guy" today. I had to sit in the back for awhile to just.... Calm down/try not to cry. It's been bothering me more and more lately.
I've been a tech for 8 years. I work in the custom PC field. I'm not brilliant or anything but I know a few things and if I don't I'm not afraid to admit it and I can usually figure it out. I've had guys buy MY builds and gush about how great they are but give the guys the credit. I know I know, I'm screaming into the void.... I'm just so tired. I've worked for corporate and it was a nightmare there too, one manager told me "oh yeah we hired you because we had to hire a girl and you're the only one that applied"
Fuuuuuuuuuck. I already have low self esteem. I'm just tired. I want out. And my coworkers defend me up and down, I'm not in a toxic work environment by any means. They're happy to say "oh you need to ask her I have no idea" but these people keep coming and I'm sick of it. Kinda just want to be a hermit, live on a hill, make some frog friends, and make little biscuits and tea and read books. 
That's a field I can get into right?

Edit: thank you all for the outpouring of love and support I woke up to this morning. I have no idea what I want to be when I grow up, but I definitely have some thinking to do. You're all awesome.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Fl9lyRo</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mnstrqn]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>∆</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Qf8P09x</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fCkMICx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.uawire.org/russian-tank-crewman-surrenders-to-ukrainian-forces-with-his-tank-for-10-000-reward

